The paper discusses challenges related to the development, deployment, and maintenance of software for science, which falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. It also touches on issues related to community building and leadership, which could be relevant to the cybernetics (cs.CY) sub-category. The use of Digital Object Identifiers and online systems like GitHub relates to the digital libraries (cs.DL) sub-category. The discussion of software licenses and attribution systems could be relevant to the cryptography (cs.CR) sub-category. Finally, the paper also touches on the development and deployment practices of software, which could be relevant to the programming languages (cs.PL) sub-category.
